I wanted to feel like all those people

552
00:42:35,136 --> 00:42:38,128
with first class tickets and pretty clothes.

553
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:46,302
I guess I wanted to feel...

554
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:50,348
Rich.

555
00:43:01,662 --> 00:43:04,324
How much would it take to feel rich?

556
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,531
I don't know.

557
00:43:11,881 --> 00:43:14,497
How much would it take to feel safe?

558
00:43:25,186 --> 00:43:26,676
You did that.

559
00:43:31,234 --> 00:43:33,225
You made me feel safe.

560
00:43:54,715 --> 00:43:56,046
Hey...

561
00:44:16,737 --> 00:44:19,319
Will you stay with me for a while?

562
00:45:47,995 --> 00:45:51,658
Why don't you take the afternoon off? You deserve it.

563
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:53,705
Spend it with that pretty wife of yours.

564
00:45:53,834 --> 00:45:56,826
Oh, shit, I forgot, she phoned last night.

565
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,836
What'd you tell her?

566
00:45:59,924 --> 00:46:02,711
That you were probably walking on the beach.

567
00:46:02,843 --> 00:46:03,923
I was.

568
00:46:04,011 --> 00:46:06,252
I guessed right then, didn't I?

569
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:15,850
Okay, Mr. McDeere. If you'll sign where the "X" is

570
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:18,352
and initial where it's marked.

571
00:46:39,672 --> 00:46:43,415
Well, well. The man from Gentleman's Quarterly.

572
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:46,584
How you doing, Ray?

