00:48:43,838 --> 00:48:46,250
Nothing's real until I tell it to Abby.

601
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:51,759
How did you ever land a job
with a brother in the joint?

602
00:49:04,900 --> 00:49:08,188
That's okay. I'd have done the same thing myself.

603
00:49:11,031 --> 00:49:15,445
You were always around for me,
Ray. All those years after Dad died.

604
00:49:15,536 --> 00:49:17,618
I'd have done the same.

605
00:49:17,705 --> 00:49:22,074
You think I'd ever tell guys around
here I got a brother in Harvard?

606
00:49:23,502 --> 00:49:25,208
Jesus, Ray.

607
00:49:25,296 --> 00:49:28,129
Hey, listen. I want you to see a friend of mine.

608
00:49:29,049 --> 00:49:32,257
His name is Eddie Lomax. He's a
private investigator in Little Rock.

609
00:49:32,344 --> 00:49:33,584
Ex-cop.

610
00:49:34,555 --> 00:49:36,261
Anything I can do for you?

611
00:49:36,348 --> 00:49:38,464
Sure. Get me out of here.

612
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,843
Where to?

613
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:47,227
Anywhere I can see a whole lot of sky.

614
00:49:48,194 --> 00:49:51,436
I can get through the days, I even eat the food.

615
00:49:52,281 --> 00:49:54,647
It's amazing how much you miss the sky.

616
00:50:04,793 --> 00:50:08,160
Ever plug one of these in only
you forgot to put the water in?

617
00:50:08,255 --> 00:50:09,370
No.

618
00:50:10,132 --> 00:50:12,965
- Do you know what happens?
- No.

619
00:50:13,052 --> 00:50:14,792
The lights go out.

620
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:22,182
He's been dying to see you since you called.

621
00:50:22,269 --> 00:50:24,430
That's what I saw. Tammy!

622
00:50:26,148 --> 00:50:28,184
Mr. Lomax will see you now.

623
00:50:31,070 --> 00:50:32,185
- Mr. McDeere.
- Yes.

624
00:50:32,279 --> 00:50:34,144
I practically went to law school with you.

625
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:37,778
Ray talked about you every
stinking day for three years.

626
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,608
I was his cellmate, he must have told you.

627
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:42,035
Did he tell you, by the way, it was statutory rape?

628
00:50:42,122 --> 00:50:45,159
She was 17. Looked 25. I got one to four.

629
00:50:45,251 --> 00:50:48,209
Sit down. Sit down. Come on. Sit down,
sit down. You want some Sweet'N Low?

630
00:50:48,295 --> 00:50:49,375
- You want some dairy cream?
- No.

631
00:50:49,463 --> 00:50:50,919
You want some sugar? You want some...

632
00:50:51,006 --> 00:50:52,371
Eddie, I've got some business

633
00:50:52,466 --> 00:50:54,047
- I'd like to go over with you here.
- Good. Good. Good.

634
00:50:54,134 --> 00:50:55,214
I owe your brother my life.

635
00:50:55,302 --> 00:50:57,714
- I'm leaving.
- Thank you, dear.

636
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:00,967
That's my secretary. She is terrific.

637
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:03,800
But she's got a nutcase for a
husband. He's a truck driver.

638
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,759
He moved here to be close to Graceland.

639
00:51:05,854 --> 00:51:07,139
The reason why, he thinks he's Elvis.

640
00:51:07,231 --> 00:51:11,395
What do you think his name is?
It's Elvis. Elvis Aaron Hemphill.

641
00:51:11,485 --> 00:51:13,396
I run across some strange things in this job.

642
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:16,775
Some things I'd never spray-paint on an overpass.

643
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:20,782
Now, what can I do for you?

644
00:51:22,955 --> 00:51:25,947
- What a nice surprise.
- Avery.

645
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:30,584
They didn't have to disturb you.
You didn't have to come down.

646
00:51:30,671 --> 00:51:32,161
Believe me, it's no bother.

647
00:51:32,256 --> 00:51:33,291
I was just looking for Mitch.

648
00:51:33,382 --> 00:51:36,624
Nina says he hasn't been in all afternoon.

649
00:51:36,719 --> 00:51:39,256
I didn't mean for her to call you.

650
00:51:40,889 --> 00:51:42,504
Didn't he come back with you?

651
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:46,388
I'll be honest with you. This
is not my area of expertise.

652
00:51:47,396 --> 00:51:51,230
- But you think it's possible?
- Anything's possible.

653
00:51:51,317 --> 00:51:54,559
I'll tell you one thing, if those
guys at the steak joint were feds,

654
00:51:54,653 --> 00:51:55,893
you better watch out for them.

655
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:59,025
'Cause they don't give a damn about you.

656
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:02,028
I get some pretty pissed off husbands in here.

657
00:52:03,037 --> 00:52:07,622
On the other hand, the lawyers at your
firm sure as hell seem accident prone.

658
00:52:09,168 --> 00:52:10,328
Okay.

659
00:52:12,087 --> 00:52:14,373
I'll see what I can find out.

660
00:52:15,466 --> 00:52:17,707
You better let me call you.

661
00:52:21,055 --> 00:52:23,637
You sure remind me of your brother.

662
00:52:25,601 --> 00:52:28,058
Ray comes up for parole in a while.

663
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:31,971
Says that he can last it.

664
00:52:32,441 --> 00:52:34,227
What do you think?

665
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:40,571
There's guys that can do all the
hard time the State gives them.

666
00:52:40,658 --> 00:52:43,991
Whatever Ray had, he used up to get this far.

667
00:52:53,337 --> 00:52:54,747
- Hi.
- Hi.

668
00:52:56,006 --> 00:52:58,463
- I didn't think you were home.
- Why not?

669
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:01,166
- No car.
- I took it in for service.

670
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:04,093
Avery brought me home.

671
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:09,099
I went to the office looking for you.

672
00:53:09,186 --> 00:53:10,471
I wasn't there.

673
00:53:10,562 --> 00:53:13,269
Apparently not. I even looked under your desk.

674
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:16,978
- Yeah, I went...
- Avery told me you were at MSU,

675
00:53:17,069 --> 00:53:18,809
at the law library.

676
00:53:18,904 --> 00:53:20,360
- Avery did.
- Avery did.

677
00:53:20,447 --> 00:53:22,779
But when I happened to spot
your car in the parking lot,

678
00:53:22,866 --> 00:53:25,198
it made him kind of edgy.

679
00:53:25,285 --> 00:53:28,618
Yeah, well, Avery didn't exactly know where I was.

680
00:53:30,165 --> 00:53:33,282
Probably thought you were with another woman.

681
00:53:39,717 --> 00:53:41,503
I went to see Ray.

682
00:53:43,470 --> 00:53:44,710
Ray?

683
00:53:46,932 --> 00:53:49,844
- Yeah.
- Just like that, after all this time?

684
00:53:50,894 --> 00:53:52,976
You were right. I've been stupid.

685
00:53:55,899 --> 00:53:58,231
I would have gone with you on Saturday.

686
00:53:58,318 --> 00:54:01,685
I know. God, I just wasn't... I wasn't thinking.

687
00:54:07,286 --> 00:54:08,742
How'd it go?

