What the hell are you doing?

906
01:11:35,708 --> 01:11:38,415
Jesus, I was just trying to make a copy of...

907
01:11:38,544 --> 01:11:43,129
They just started this. You have to
have the billing code for each client.

908
01:11:43,216 --> 01:11:45,798
You mean every time I copy a
piece of paper, it's recorded?

909
01:11:45,885 --> 01:11:47,591
What are you trying to do, kill yourself?

910
01:11:47,720 --> 01:11:50,382
Come on. Nina should do that anyway.

911
01:11:51,349 --> 01:11:54,011
Come down for one night, can't you?

912
01:11:55,561 --> 01:11:57,893
Well, it used to be worth it.

913
01:12:01,234 --> 01:12:05,398
Okay. Yeah, maybe next time.

914
01:12:06,072 --> 01:12:07,778
Bye, Cordelia.

915
01:12:09,075 --> 01:12:10,315
That was Cordelia.

916
01:12:10,409 --> 01:12:12,570
Yeah. Your wife.

917
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:14,322
From the song of the same name.

918
01:12:14,413 --> 01:12:17,496
Avery, I have a couple of ideas about those Capps LCs.

919
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,869
When's the next Cayman trip?

920
01:12:20,586 --> 01:12:22,827
For me? Next week.

921
01:12:22,922 --> 01:12:26,631
If you think I'm gonna let Sonny Capps
get another look at you, you're crazy.

922
01:12:26,759 --> 01:12:28,295
But you write down every single thought you have.

923
01:12:28,427 --> 01:12:30,759
I'll be happy to take credit.

924
01:12:32,765 --> 01:12:37,259
Mr. McDeere! Mr. Mulholland's
called twice about his bills again.

925
01:12:37,395 --> 01:12:40,353
Tell Mr. Mulholland to take his bill and...

926
01:12:40,439 --> 01:12:42,725
No, wait a minute, wait a minute.
Isn't he just up the street?

927
01:12:42,817 --> 01:12:44,728
- Yes. In the Cotton Exchange.
- Cotton Exchange.

928
01:12:44,819 --> 01:12:46,855
Tell him I'll see him later.

929
01:12:46,946 --> 01:12:49,858
Did you order a fried egg sandwich
from the Front Street Deli?

930
01:12:49,949 --> 01:12:51,735
A fried egg...

931
01:12:57,415 --> 01:12:59,497
Yes, I did. I did.

932
01:13:00,835 --> 01:13:02,291
Come in.

933
01:13:04,589 --> 01:13:07,581
It's $2.65. The receipt's in the bag.

934
01:13:14,765 --> 01:13:16,801
The receipt's in the bag.

935
01:13:36,454 --> 01:13:38,866
How did you see them, and they didn't see you?

936
01:13:38,998 --> 01:13:40,863
I was under the desk.

937
01:13:45,046 --> 01:13:48,880
I was vacuuming the rug. You
want me to draw you a diagram?

938
01:13:50,551 --> 01:13:52,041
I loved him.

939
01:13:54,180 --> 01:13:55,841
I'm sorry, Tammy.

940
01:13:59,060 --> 01:14:00,175
They wanted to know who hired him

941
01:14:00,311 --> 01:14:03,724
and why he was asking questions about dead lawyers.

942
01:14:08,653 --> 01:14:10,564
You actually saw them?

943
01:14:13,324 --> 01:14:16,862
One guy was stocky, looked like a wrestler.

944
01:14:17,662 --> 01:14:20,199
He's gonna limp the rest of his life

945
01:14:20,331 --> 01:14:24,495
'cause Eddie hit him in the knee
with that cannon under his desk.

946
01:14:25,544 --> 01:14:28,707
And the other guy was like an albino.

947
01:14:31,050 --> 01:14:34,918
Long thin hair, almost white.

948
01:14:35,554 --> 01:14:37,215
Dead blue eyes.

949
01:14:39,725 --> 01:14:41,681
My landlady said they came looking for me yesterday,

950
01:14:41,769 --> 01:14:43,475
so I checked into the Motel 6 on River Street.

951
01:14:43,562 --> 01:14:46,429
I couldn't think of anywhere else to go.

952
01:14:49,568 --> 01:14:53,686
Listen, they're gonna put Eddie
together with Ray, and when they do,

953
01:14:54,407 --> 01:14:56,238
it'll lead to you.

954
01:14:57,702 --> 01:15:00,068
I don't want anything bad to happen to you.

955
01:15:00,204 --> 01:15:02,286
Eddie wouldn't like it.

956
01:15:02,415 --> 01:15:05,202
So, you're in as much trouble as I am.

957
01:15:06,585 --> 01:15:10,703
Listen, there's a building around
the corner called the Cotton Exchange.

958
01:15:10,798 --> 01:15:12,288
Maybe you can help, Tammy.

959
01:15:16,303 --> 01:15:17,543
Hi there, Mitch.

960
01:15:17,638 --> 01:15:20,505
Bill Devasher, Firm Security.

961
01:15:20,599 --> 01:15:25,059
Mr. Locke and Mr. Lambert were telling
me about your little run in with the FBI.

962
01:15:25,146 --> 01:15:27,853
I wonder if we could have a little talk.

963
01:15:27,940 --> 01:15:29,931
Actually, I told them everything.

964
01:15:30,067 --> 01:15:32,979
I'm sure you did. This won't take a minute.

965
01:15:40,619 --> 01:15:41,984
Hop in.

966
01:16:12,276 --> 01:16:14,642
So, Mitch, this is a debriefing.

967
01:16:18,324 --> 01:16:20,940
I know pretty much what you told the fellows,

968
01:16:21,035 --> 01:16:23,321
so I kind of got the picture.

969
01:16:23,454 --> 01:16:26,287
Now it's my job to give you the picture.

970
01:16:26,373 --> 01:16:29,160
What I'm concerned about, son, is this.

971
01:16:29,293 --> 01:16:32,126
The FBI wouldn't have come after you
if they didn't figure they'd get to you.

972
01:16:32,213 --> 01:16:34,374
What do you suppose made them think that?

973
01:16:34,507 --> 01:16:35,872
I have no idea.

974
01:16:36,008 --> 01:16:38,841
Well, see, it's my job to have an idea about that.

975
01:16:38,969 --> 01:16:42,382
