1282
01:41:23,661 --> 01:41:24,992
Really?

1283
01:41:26,330 --> 01:41:28,321
I'd heard that you don't miss a chance to...

1284
01:41:28,457 --> 01:41:29,822
Not this time.

1285
01:41:29,959 --> 01:41:32,746
I had to shorten the trip, clients coming into town.

1286
01:41:32,837 --> 01:41:36,421
I can't dive and fly in the same 24 hours. So, you see?

1287
01:41:37,508 --> 01:41:39,339
How about it?

1288
01:41:40,845 --> 01:41:42,836
My mother isn't well.

1289
01:41:44,432 --> 01:41:46,514
They're doing some tests.

1290
01:41:47,018 --> 01:41:49,680
That's why I'm going home.

1291
01:41:50,021 --> 01:41:52,137
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

1292
01:41:53,024 --> 01:41:55,106
How could you possibly?

1293
01:41:56,360 --> 01:42:01,320
I hope she feels better, and
if she does, bring her with you.

1294
01:42:04,702 --> 01:42:08,035
Goodbye, Avery. Have a good flight.

1295
01:42:17,632 --> 01:42:19,372
Greenwood Secretarial Services.

1296
01:42:19,508 --> 01:42:22,716
Tammy, this is Abby McDeere. I
think you've got a serious problem.

1297
01:42:22,803 --> 01:42:24,839
Avery's not going diving.

1298
01:42:26,724 --> 01:42:28,214
We're dead.

1299
01:42:31,228 --> 01:42:33,219
Well, how do we...

1300
01:42:35,691 --> 01:42:37,898
How am I gonna tell Mitch? How am I gonna let him know?

1301
01:42:46,410 --> 01:42:49,322
I'm going anyway. I've got to try to do something.

1302
01:42:49,413 --> 01:42:51,870
My flight's in three hours.

1303
01:42:58,589 --> 01:43:00,250
Mr. McDeere's office.

1304
01:43:00,883 --> 01:43:02,748
I'm sorry, he's not in. May I take a message?

1305
01:43:20,111 --> 01:43:22,602
Tammy, don't tell Mitch anything.

1306
01:43:26,784 --> 01:43:28,695
I'll just be a sec.

1307
01:43:30,121 --> 01:43:32,737
A prescription for Abigail McDeere.

1308
01:43:49,306 --> 01:43:50,637
One!

1309
01:43:54,061 --> 01:43:57,144
Well, you want to go, or do you want to stay here?

1310
01:43:57,231 --> 01:44:00,644
- Aren't you gonna cuff him?
- I'll take care of it.

1311
01:44:12,747 --> 01:44:14,237
Yeah?

1312
01:44:14,331 --> 01:44:16,492
Guess what I'm looking at?

1313
01:44:17,918 --> 01:44:19,249
Tell me.

1314
01:44:19,795 --> 01:44:22,332
My first sunset in six years.

1315
01:44:24,508 --> 01:44:26,339
- You made it.
- Yeah.

1316
01:44:27,511 --> 01:44:29,251
Yeah, I did.

1317
01:44:29,346 --> 01:44:31,507
I owe you, little brother.

1318
01:44:33,350 --> 01:44:34,931
No, you don't.

1319
01:44:37,772 --> 01:44:41,014
- Anything from Abanks?
- Last I heard, everything was set.

1320
01:44:42,026 --> 01:44:43,937
It's gonna be fine.

1321
01:44:45,279 --> 01:44:46,860
It already is.

1322
01:44:50,451 --> 01:44:52,282
I'll be seeing you, Ray.

1323
01:44:54,038 --> 01:44:56,780
Okay, you spoke to him. Now, where are the files?

1324
01:44:56,874 --> 01:44:58,114
Where's the money?

1325
01:44:58,209 --> 01:44:59,699
Not until I get the files.

1326
01:44:59,794 --> 01:45:01,534
You send half now.

1327
01:45:01,670 --> 01:45:05,788
Account number 6194408S. You got that?

1328
01:45:06,300 --> 01:45:10,384
Yeah. 6194408S, yeah.

1329
01:45:11,180 --> 01:45:14,968
When I get confirmation it's
there, I'll send the files.

1330
01:45:23,234 --> 01:45:25,566
Here's some pocket money.

1331
01:45:25,694 --> 01:45:29,312
You're free, McDeere. There's
a bus stop a quarter mile.

1332
01:45:29,406 --> 01:45:32,398
Follow the yellow line. You're used to that.

1333
01:46:19,164 --> 01:46:20,825
Excuse me.

1334
01:46:39,643 --> 01:46:42,180
You don't seem that surprised.

1335
01:46:42,271 --> 01:46:44,182
I'm deeply surprised.

1336
01:46:46,066 --> 01:46:47,351
So am I.

1337
01:46:59,538 --> 01:47:01,654
Stephanie, could we have two Havana Club, please?

1338
01:47:01,749 --> 01:47:03,330
Yes, Mr. Tolar.

1339
01:47:18,015 --> 01:47:20,347
How'd the test turn out?

1340
01:47:20,434 --> 01:47:23,050
We were worried for no reason.

1341
01:47:23,187 --> 01:47:24,347
Good.

1342
01:47:26,523 --> 01:47:30,186
I didn't think we'd got on
that well in the school yard.

1343
01:47:31,695 --> 01:47:34,277
Maybe I've grown up since then.

1344
01:47:34,365 --> 01:47:36,447
I'd love to believe that.

1345
01:47:55,552 --> 01:47:57,884
- It's delicious.
- Isn't it?

1346
01:47:57,972 --> 01:47:59,712
It's like cognac.

1347
01:48:01,600 --> 01:48:04,387
You know, I have a very bad reputation.

1348
01:48:07,773 --> 01:48:10,139
- What do you do?
- I run around.

1349
01:48:11,443 --> 01:48:13,274
Why do you do that?

1350
01:48:16,240 --> 01:48:19,232
I think it's because my wife understands me.

1351
01:48:24,248 --> 01:48:26,409
The fact is, I love my wife.

1352
01:48:30,421 --> 01:48:34,084
But she's... Well, I guess she's lost interest in me.

1353
01:48:34,800 --> 01:48:36,415
I know I have.

1354
01:48:40,305 --> 01:48:43,672
And I haven't cared for anyone since.

1355
01:48:46,603 --> 01:48:48,434
I'd like to, though.

1356
01:48:49,815 --> 01:48:51,180
I miss it.

1357
01:48:56,864 --> 01:48:59,981
My, you lay a lot on a girl for a first date.

1358
01:49:01,618 --> 01:49:03,449
Is that what this is?

1359
01:49:12,713 --> 01:49:13,748
This is Unit B.

1360
01:49:13,839 --> 01:49:17,878
We'll be pulling into Five Points
at 11:15 for a 20-minute rest stop.

1361
01:49:17,968 --> 01:49:19,959
Mrs. Sunderland, I'm sorry to call you at home so late,

1362
01:49:20,054 --> 01:49:23,046
but I need to speak to you
about something that's, well,

1363
01:49:23,140 --> 01:49:24,676
it's really quite embarrassing.

1364
01:49:24,808 --> 01:49:27,345
Let me preface this by saying you're
not the only client at the Firm

1365
01:49:27,478 --> 01:49:28,558
that I've had to call about this.

1366
01:50:40,467 --> 01:50:43,880
I'd like a big steak, medium
rare, three fried eggs over,

1367
01:50:43,971 --> 01:50:46,383
French fries and coffee, please.

1368
01:50:50,894 --> 01:50:53,476
I'll see you, darling.

1369
01:52:03,091 --> 01:52:04,456
Fuck!

1370
01:52:21,526 --> 01:52:23,938
What the hell is going on? We lost your brother.

1371
01:52:24,029 --> 01:52:26,190
Why, were you following him?

1372
01:52:26,323 --> 01:52:28,279
Are you trying to fuck with me?

1373
01:52:28,367 --> 01:52:29,777
Where are you? Where are those files?

1374
01:52:29,868 --> 01:52:33,326
Are you trying to fuck with me? You
want the files, you wire the money.

1375
01:52:33,455 --> 01:52:34,991
I want those files now.

1376
01:52:35,123 --> 01:52:36,954
Got to go, Wayne.

1377
01:52:39,336 --> 01:52:42,123
He knows exactly where his brother is.

1378
01:52:43,215 --> 01:52:44,705
Have them check all the credit cards

1379
01:52:44,841 --> 01:52:48,379
of everybody that got fuel outside
that diner between 11:00 and 11:45,

1380
01:52:48,512 --> 01:52:50,753
whenever we lost Ray.

1381
01:52:50,847 --> 01:52:52,132
There couldn't be more than a dozen or so.

1382
01:52:52,224 --> 01:52:54,135
He's got to be on one of them.

1383
01:52:54,226 --> 01:52:56,558
And get me a map of Louisiana.

1384
01:52:58,355 --> 01:53:00,346
Get me a map of Louisiana!

1385
01:53:38,395 --> 01:53:40,556
It hasn't even begun to melt.

1386
01:53:41,523 --> 01:53:44,105
The staff was chosen for its timing.

1387
01:54:35,577 --> 01:54:38,489
I would do that, but I could never do that.

1388
01:54:39,956 --> 01:54:42,117
The buttons are too small.

1389
01:54:44,086 --> 01:54:46,577
It requires terrible...

1390
01:54:46,671 --> 01:54:48,161
Dexterity.

1391
01:54:50,926 --> 01:54:52,632
Amazing.

1392
01:55:04,481 --> 01:55:06,096
What are you doing here?

1393
01:55:06,191 --> 01:55:07,806
What do you mean?

1394
01:55:07,943 --> 01:55:10,559
I mean, exactly what did you come here for?

1395
01:55:10,654 --> 01:55:12,815
I thought I was invited.

1396
01:55:13,198 --> 01:55:15,359
You're not being truthful.

1397
01:55:17,494 --> 01:55:19,985
Why are you doing this?

1398
01:55:20,330 --> 01:55:25,040
Because I'm sick and I want you to tell me the truth.

1399
01:55:27,003 --> 01:55:31,167
I came here to punish Mitch for
letting the Firm ruin our lives.

1400
01:55:32,509 --> 01:55:36,127
I came because when Mitch was here
with you he slept with someone else.

1401
01:55:36,221 --> 01:55:38,553
Is that what you want to hear?

1402
01:55:44,688 --> 01:55:47,304
That's better than the alternative.

1403
01:55:48,024 --> 01:55:49,764
What alternative?

1404
01:55:50,819 --> 01:55:53,151
That you came here to see me.

1405
01:56:21,224 --> 01:56:22,464
Avery?

1406
01:56:57,677 --> 01:56:59,918
It came in about three hours ago.

1407
01:57:00,013 --> 01:57:01,674
You sure he'll be all right?

1408
01:57:01,765 --> 01:57:03,926
What the hell you want to do? Call 911?

1409
01:57:04,017 --> 01:57:07,509
Get the key, grab the stuff and get over here.

1410
01:57:07,604 --> 01:57:09,094
Keep calling him.

1411
01:57:09,189 --> 01:57:12,272
Wake the son of a bitch up. When
you get him on the phone, find me.

1412
01:57:12,400 --> 01:57:13,435
I want that girl.

1413
01:57:19,282 --> 01:57:23,525
The account number is 6194408S.

1414
01:57:25,121 --> 01:57:28,454
And can you confirm that it is $ 750,000?

1415
01:57:49,145 --> 01:57:52,262
Absolutely. I'm fixing to get out of here now.

1416
01:57:53,066 --> 01:57:54,556
You got all the information I need?

1417
01:57:54,651 --> 01:57:57,893
Yeah, but, Mitch...

1418
01:57:57,988 --> 01:58:02,152
I've been looking at this stuff
and there's no numbers listed.

1419
01:58:02,242 --> 01:58:04,483
There's no numbers? No amounts?

1420
01:58:04,578 --> 01:58:06,569
No, I got papers for bank accounts everywhere

1421
01:58:06,663 --> 01:58:10,155
from the Caymans to Hong Kong, but there's no amounts.

1422
01:58:12,127 --> 01:58:14,584
I can't play the poker game I'm gonna play and bluff.

1423
01:58:14,671 --> 01:58:17,162
I gotta know how much they have and where.

1424
01:58:17,257 --> 01:58:20,169
There's a note on each one that says,

1425
01:58:21,011 --> 01:58:24,503
"Info held by client and my Mac. Signed A.T."

1426
01:58:24,639 --> 01:58:27,506
Is there any other information? Is there a password?

1427
01:58:27,642 --> 01:58:30,008
Some kind of password? Just look on the paper, Tammy.

1428
01:58:30,103 --> 01:58:31,764
Wait a minute.

1429
01:58:31,855 --> 01:58:35,097
On the side of one, in parenthesis it says,

1430
01:58:35,191 --> 01:58:39,685
"R-E-F," then a colon, then, "Cordelia."

1431
01:58:40,447 --> 01:58:43,359
Okay, okay, I've got to get to Avery's
computer in the morning before I leave.

1432
01:58:43,491 --> 01:58:44,776
Well, listen, be careful.

1433
01:58:44,868 --> 01:58:47,280
We don't know how this is
all gonna look in the morning.

1434
01:58:47,370 --> 01:58:49,531
I should be able to get through the morning fine.

1435
01:58:49,664 --> 01:58:52,371
By the time they notice I'm not
back from lunch, I'll be in Chicago.

1436
01:59:00,842 --> 01:59:03,629
Okay. We're finished. That's it.
I gotta get these out to the boat.

1437
01:59:03,720 --> 01:59:05,335
The boat?

1438
01:59:06,139 --> 01:59:07,970
- What boat?
- Oh, man.

1439
01:59:09,351 --> 01:59:11,967
Later on there's some stuff I gotta
tell you about what Mitch is doing.

1440
01:59:12,062 --> 01:59:13,393
Tell me now, Tammy. What?

1441
01:59:13,480 --> 01:59:16,643
Get the damn keys back in his pants
and get out of there before he wakes up.

1442
01:59:36,252 --> 01:59:37,788
Hello?

1443
01:59:42,300 --> 01:59:44,541
You have to repeat that.

1444
01:59:48,848 --> 01:59:50,258
That's not possible.

1445
01:59:50,350 --> 01:59:53,342
She stole your keys and God knows what else.

1446
01:59:53,978 --> 01:59:56,060
Now who the hell is she?

1447
01:59:56,147 --> 01:59:59,105
You know me,

1448
01:59:59,192 --> 02:00:01,478
just somebody I met last night.

1449
02:00:01,569 --> 02:00:04,276
Then how the hell does she know to go after your keys?

1450
02:00:04,364 --> 02:00:07,948
The guys will be landing in about
10 minutes and she better be there.

1451
02:00:40,734 --> 02:00:41,940
Don't.

1452
02:00:44,154 --> 02:00:46,395
They heard you on the phone.

1453
02:00:50,994 --> 02:00:52,609
Mitch sent you.

1454
02:00:57,584 --> 02:00:59,825
I knew he was a closet idealist.

1455
02:00:59,919 --> 02:01:02,001
He doesn't know I'm here.

1456
02:01:03,965 --> 02:01:06,047
But I did do it for him.

1457
02:01:06,760 --> 02:01:09,877
That's even better than getting even with him.

1458
02:01:12,515 --> 02:01:14,255
You gotta get out of here.

1459
02:01:21,357 --> 02:01:23,063
What are you going to do?

1460
02:01:23,151 --> 02:01:25,517
Abby, the girl was a set-up.

1461
02:01:27,280 --> 02:01:29,692
On the beach, she was a set-up.

1462
02:01:32,660 --> 02:01:34,776
They do things like that.

1463
02:01:35,455 --> 02:01:38,572
Just in case the usual inducements don't work.

1464
02:01:41,044 --> 02:01:44,127
What's going to happen? What
are they going to do to you?

1465
02:01:44,214 --> 02:01:46,170
Whatever it is...

1466
02:01:48,760 --> 02:01:50,796
They did it a long time ago.

1467
02:01:52,680 --> 02:01:54,011
Get this thing out of here, will you?

1468
02:01:54,098 --> 02:01:56,305
Look, this ain't your cotton
truck, and this ain't your alley!

1469
02:01:56,392 --> 02:01:58,599
I'm calling in to the Department of Traffic right now!

1470
02:01:58,686 --> 02:01:59,892
They call?

1471
02:01:59,979 --> 02:02:01,435
Not yet.

1472
02:02:05,652 --> 02:02:07,517
Madge, I just talked to Avery in the Caymans.

1473
02:02:07,612 --> 02:02:09,773
He needs some work done on
the Kemmer papers before 10:00.

1474
02:02:09,864 --> 02:02:12,025
I'll just get it off his computer.

1475
02:02:17,163 --> 02:02:18,403
What the hell's the matter with you guys?

1476
02:02:18,498 --> 02:02:20,659
This thing's out of paper.

1477
02:02:37,976 --> 02:02:39,341
McDeere in yet?

1478
02:02:39,435 --> 02:02:41,721
Check every goddamn floor and find him.

1479
02:02:41,813 --> 02:02:43,519
That son of a bitch cut a deal.

1480
02:02:53,157 --> 02:02:57,992
- Natisin, Earlywine, Hemphill.
- Hemphill?

1481
02:02:58,454 --> 02:02:59,785
Wait a minute. That's Lomax's secretary.

1482
02:02:59,873 --> 02:03:02,990
Wayne, it's Warden Dynehart from Wrightsville prison.

1483
02:03:04,168 --> 02:03:06,705
Wayne, we've got a problem here.
I've just been questioning a guard

1484
02:03:06,796 --> 02:03:09,458
who sent an unauthorized fax to a law firm in Memphis

1485
02:03:09,549 --> 02:03:11,505
and I think it was in regard to your prisoner.

1486
02:03:11,593 --> 02:03:14,460
No! No, no, no, no!

1487
02:03:23,730 --> 02:03:26,642
No, he's not in his office, Your
Honor. I'll see if he's in the building.

1488
02:03:31,654 --> 02:03:33,110
- Thank you, Madge.
- You're welcome.

1489
02:03:33,197 --> 02:03:34,562
Mitch...

1490
02:03:35,867 --> 02:03:38,279
We've just been looking for you.

1491
02:03:39,662 --> 02:03:41,948
Can you step in here, please?

1492
02:03:43,249 --> 02:03:47,834
Mr. Tolar's office. Yes, he's
right here. Nina, transfer him.

